The paper deals with the problem of anonymizing tables containing personal information, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The problem is related to privacy and security, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The $k$-anonymization problem is a combinatorial optimization problem, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses techniques from information theory to derive bounds on the approximation ratio, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
